Param.Name: BladePitchMax
Param.Description: The maximum positive blade pitch in degrees - this affects the max ascent rate of the aircraft AND max forward speed; works in conjunction with CollectivePower

Param.Name: BladePitchMin
Param.Description: The maximum negative blade pitch in degrees - this mainly affects the max descent rate of the aircraft; works in conjunction with CollectivePower

Param.Name: BladeRPM
Param.Description: The RPM of the main rotor at normal hovering / forward flight (usually the RPM at 80% throttle); note this is purely visual and does not have an effect on performance

Param.Name: CeilingAltitude
Param.Description: Altitude in metres that the helicopter will no longer provide any lift (the lift begins dropping off from 50m away from this height)

Param.Name: CollectivePower
Param.Description: This value dictates the max rate at which the heli can rise and descend and works in conjunction with BladePitchMin/Max; in turn determines max forward-flight speed

Param.Name: CollectiveSens
Param.Description: Collective senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of collective input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: CyclicPower
Param.Description: This value dictates the cyclic power, ie the max rate of roll and pitch (from aileron and elevator input)

Param.Name: CyclicSens
Param.Description: Cyclic senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of aileron and elevator input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: ElevToRuddMix
Param.Description: When performing a banked turn, this value determines how much it also turns (yaws) from purely elevator input, helping the turn; works together with WeatherVane

Param.Name: GroundEffect
Param.Description: Ground effect multiplier. A value of 1.0 means it has a simulation level of ground effect (see RotorDiameter). Caution! Increasing above 1 may cause difficulty in landing

Param.Name: GyroscopeFactor
Param.Description: Gyroscopic resistance to cyclic and rudder input; can also be thought of as angular damping, ie. governs the rate at which it will stop when removing cyclic/rudder input

Param.Name: RotorDiameter
Param.Description: The diameter of the main rotor disc. This affects the ground effect, which begins at 1.25 x diameter and is +7% at 0.5 diameter [with a GroundEffect of 1.0]

Param.Name: RotSpinUpTime
Param.Description: The time in seconds that it takes to spin up the rotor from 0rpm to BladeRPM having started the engine; also effects spin-down time (which is roughly twice this time)

Param.Name: RudderPower
Param.Description: This value dictates the power of the rudder, ie the max rate of yaw from rudder input (ie vertical rotation)

Param.Name: RudderSens
Param.Description: Rudder senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of rudder input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: SelfLevelling
Param.Description: This value dictates how much the helicopter self-levels with zero cyclic input (note this is not speed dependant)

Param.Name: StabilizerAngle
Param.Description: This is the downward angle in degrees of the rear horizontal stabilizer (which dictates natural forward-pitch flight angle tendency proportional to forward speed)

Param.Name: TailDiameter
Param.Description: The diameter of the tail rotor disc

Param.Name: WeatherVane
Param.Description: This value determines how much the tail naturally trails behind like the flight of a dart (works in conjunction with above)

Param.Name: waterFillRate
Param.Description: The rate at which water enters the vehicle once

Param.Description: This value has to match the componentID of the weapon mount

Param.Name: BladePitchMax
Param.Description: The maximum positive blade pitch in degrees - this affects the max ascent rate of the aircraft AND max forward speed; works in conjunction with CollectivePower

Param.Name: BladePitchMin
Param.Description: The maximum negative blade pitch in degrees - this mainly affects the max descent rate of the aircraft; works in conjunction with CollectivePower

Param.Name: BladeRPM
Param.Description: The RPM of the main rotor at normal hovering / forward flight (usually the RPM at 80% throttle); note this is purely visual and does not have an effect on performance

Param.Name: CeilingAltitude
Param.Description: Altitude in metres that the helicopter will no longer provide any lift (the lift begins dropping off from 50m away from this height)

Param.Name: CollectivePower
Param.Description: This value dictates the max rate at which the heli can rise and descend and works in conjunction with BladePitchMin/Max; in turn determines max forward-flight speed

Param.Name: CollectiveSens
Param.Description: Collective senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of collective input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: CyclicPower
Param.Description: This value dictates the cyclic power, ie the max rate of roll and pitch (from aileron and elevator input)

Param.Name: CyclicSens
Param.Description: Cyclic senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of aileron and elevator input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: ElevToRuddMix
Param.Description: When performing a banked turn, this value determines how much it also turns (yaws) from purely elevator input, helping the turn; works together with WeatherVane

Param.Name: GroundEffect
Param.Description: Ground effect multiplier. A value of 1.0 means it has a simulation level of ground effect (see RotorDiameter). Caution! Increasing above 1 may cause difficulty in landing

Param.Name: GyroscopeFactor
Param.Description: Gyroscopic resistance to cyclic and rudder input; can also be thought of as angular damping, ie. governs the rate at which it will stop when removing cyclic/rudder input

Param.Name: RotorDiameter
Param.Description: The diameter of the main rotor disc. This affects the ground effect, which begins at 1.25 x diameter and is +7% at 0.5 diameter [with a GroundEffect of 1.0]

Param.Name: RotSpinUpTime
Param.Description: The time in seconds that it takes to spin up the rotor from 0rpm to BladeRPM having started the engine; also effects spin-down time (which is roughly twice this time)

Param.Name: RudderPower
Param.Description: This value dictates the power of the rudder, ie the max rate of yaw from rudder input (ie vertical rotation)

Param.Name: RudderSens
Param.Description: Rudder senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of rudder input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: SelfLevelling
Param.Description: This value dictates how much the helicopter self-levels with zero cyclic input (note this is not speed dependant)

Param.Name: StabilizerAngle
Param.Description: This is the downward angle in degrees of the rear horizontal stabilizer (which dictates natural forward-pitch flight angle tendency proportional to forward speed)

Param.Name: TailDiameter
Param.Description: The diameter of the tail rotor disc

Param.Name: WeatherVane
Param.Description: This value determines how much the tail naturally trails behind like the flight of a dart (works in conjunction with above)

Param.Name: waterFillRate
Param.Description: The rate at which water enters the vehicle once

Param.Name: CollectivePower
Param.Description: This value dictates the max rate at which the heli can rise and descend and works in conjunction with BladePitchMin/Max; in turn determines max forward-flight speed

Param.Name: CyclicPower
Param.Description: This value dictates the cyclic power, ie the max rate of roll and pitch (from aileron and elevator input)

Param.Name: GyroscopeFactor
Param.Description: Gyroscopic resistance to cyclic and rudder input; can also be thought of as angular damping, ie. governs the rate at which it will stop when removing cyclic/rudder input

Param.Name: RotorClockwise
Param.Description: Whether the main rotor spins clockwise (when viewed from above). Set to False to make the rotor spin counter-clockwise. Also reverses the tail rotor.

Param.Name: RotorDiameter
Param.Description: The diameter of the main rotor disc. This affects the ground effect, which begins at 1.25 x diameter and is +7% at 0.5 diameter [with a GroundEffect of 1.0]

Param.Name: RudderPower
Param.Description: This value dictates the power of the rudder, ie the max rate of yaw from rudder input (ie vertical rotation)

Param.Name: RudderSens
Param.Description: Rudder senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of rudder input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: SelfLevelling
Param.Description: This value dictates how much the helicopter self-levels with zero cyclic input (note this is not speed dependant)

Param.Name: TailDiameter
Param.Description: The diameter of the tail rotor disc

Param.Name: WeatherVane
Param.Description: This value determines how much the tail naturally trails behind like the flight of a dart (works in conjunction with RudderPower)

Param.Name: CollectivePower
Param.Description: This value dictates the max rate at which the heli can rise and descend and works in conjunction with BladePitchMin/Max; in turn determines max forward-flight speed

Param.Name: CyclicPower
Param.Description: This value dictates the cyclic power, ie the max rate of roll and pitch (from aileron and elevator input)

Param.Name: GyroscopeFactor
Param.Description: Gyroscopic resistance to cyclic and rudder input; can also be thought of as angular damping, ie. governs the rate at which it will stop when removing cyclic/rudder input

Param.Name: RudderSens
Param.Description: Rudder senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of rudder input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: SelfLevelling
Param.Description: This value dictates how much the helicopter self-levels with zero cyclic input (note this is not speed dependant)

Param.Name: WeatherVane
Param.Description: This value determines how much the tail naturally trails behind like the flight of a dart (works in conjunction with RudderPower)

Param.Name: BladePitchMax
Param.Description: The maximum positive blade pitch in degrees - this affects the max ascent rate of the aircraft AND max forward speed; works in conjunction with CollectivePower

Param.Name: BladePitchMin
Param.Description: The maximum negative blade pitch in degrees - this mainly affects the max descent rate of the aircraft; works in conjunction with CollectivePower

Param.Name: BladeRPM
Param.Description: The RPM of the main rotor at normal hovering / forward flight (usually the RPM at 80% throttle); note this is purely visual and does not have an effect on performance

Param.Name: CeilingAltitude
Param.Description: Altitude in metres that the helicopter will no longer provide any lift (the lift begins dropping off from 50m away from this height)

Param.Name: CollectivePower
Param.Description: This value dictates the max rate at which the heli can rise and descend and works in conjunction with BladePitchMin/Max; in turn determines max forward-flight speed

Param.Name: CollectiveSens
Param.Description: Collective senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of collective input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: CyclicPower
Param.Description: This value dictates the cyclic power, ie the max rate of roll and pitch (from aileron and elevator input)

Param.Name: CyclicSens
Param.Description: Cyclic senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of aileron and elevator input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: ElevToRuddMix
Param.Description: When performing a banked turn, this value determines how much it also turns (yaws) from purely elevator input, helping the turn; works together with WeatherVane

Param.Name: EntryThreshold
Param.Description: This is the distance threshold to the entry point which you are able to enter to a vehicle

Param.Name: GroundEffect
Param.Description: Ground effect multiplier. A value of 1.0 means it has a simulation level of ground effect (see RotorDiameter). Caution! Increasing above 1 may cause difficulty in landing

Param.Name: GyroscopeFactor
Param.Description: Gyroscopic resistance to cyclic and rudder input; can also be thought of as angular damping, ie. governs the rate at which it will stop when removing cyclic/rudder input

Param.Name: RotorDiameter
Param.Description: The diameter of the main rotor disc. This affects the ground effect, which begins at 1.25 x diameter and is +7% at 0.5 diameter [with a GroundEffect of 1.0]

Param.Name: RotSpinUpTime
Param.Description: The time in seconds that it takes to spin up the rotor from 0rpm to BladeRPM having started the engine; also effects spin-down time (which is roughly twice this time)

Param.Name: RudderPower
Param.Description: This value dictates the power of the rudder, ie the max rate of yaw from rudder input (ie vertical rotation)

Param.Name: RudderSens
Param.Description: Rudder senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of rudder input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: SelfLevelling
Param.Description: This value dictates how much the helicopter self-levels with zero cyclic input (note this is not speed dependant)

Param.Name: StabilizerAngle
Param.Description: This is the downward angle in degrees of the rear horizontal stabilizer (which dictates natural forward-pitch flight angle tendency proportional to forward speed)

Param.Name: TailDiameter
Param.Description: The diameter of the tail rotor disc

Param.Name: WeatherVane
Param.Description: This value determines how much the tail naturally trails behind like the flight of a dart (works in conjunction with above)

Param.Name: waterFillRate
Param.Description: The rate at which water enters the vehicle once

Param.Name: MountName1
Param.Description: This value has to match the componentID of the weapon mount

Param.Name: MountName1
Param.Description: This value has to match the componentID of the weapon mount

Param.Description: Event Name for Tail Rotor

Param.Name: BladePitchMax
Param.Description: The maximum positive blade pitch in degrees - this affects the max ascent rate of the aircraft AND max forward speed; works in conjunction with CollectivePower

Param.Name: BladePitchMin
Param.Description: The maximum negative blade pitch in degrees - this mainly affects the max descent rate of the aircraft; works in conjunction with CollectivePower

Param.Name: BladeRPM
Param.Description: The RPM of the main rotor at normal hovering / forward flight (usually the RPM at 80% throttle); note this is purely visual and does not have an effect on performance

Param.Name: CeilingAltitude
Param.Description: Altitude in metres that the helicopter will no longer provide any lift (the lift begins dropping off from 50m away from this height)

Param.Name: CollectivePower
Param.Description: This value dictates the max rate at which the heli can rise and descend and works in conjunction with BladePitchMin/Max; in turn determines max forward-flight speed

Param.Name: CollectiveSens
Param.Description: Collective senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of collective input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: CyclicPower
Param.Description: This value dictates the cyclic power, ie the max rate of roll and pitch (from aileron and elevator input)

Param.Name: CyclicSens
Param.Description: Cyclic senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of aileron and elevator input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: ElevToRuddMix
Param.Description: When performing a banked turn, this value determines how much it also turns (yaws) from purely elevator input, helping the turn; works together with WeatherVane

Param.Name: EntryThreshold
Param.Description: This is the distance threshold to the entry point which you are able to enter to a vehicle

Param.Name: GroundEffect
Param.Description: Ground effect multiplier. A value of 1.0 means it has a simulation level of ground effect (see RotorDiameter). Caution! Increasing above 1 may cause difficulty in landing

Param.Name: GyroscopeFactor
Param.Description: Gyroscopic resistance to cyclic and rudder input; can also be thought of as angular damping, ie. governs the rate at which it will stop when removing cyclic/rudder input

Param.Name: RotorClockwise
Param.Description: Whether the main rotor spins clockwise (when viewed from above). Set to False to make the rotor spin counter-clockwise. Also reverses the tail rotor.

Param.Name: RotorDiameter
Param.Description: The diameter of the main rotor disc. This affects the ground effect, which begins at 1.25 x diameter and is +7% at 0.5 diameter [with a GroundEffect of 1.0]

Param.Name: RotSpinUpTime
Param.Description: The time in seconds that it takes to spin up the rotor from 0rpm to BladeRPM having started the engine; also effects spin-down time (which is roughly twice this time)

Param.Name: RudderPower
Param.Description: This value dictates the power of the rudder, ie the max rate of yaw from rudder input (ie vertical rotation)

Param.Name: RudderSens
Param.Description: Rudder senstitivity, ie the responsiveness of rudder input, determines how quickly full input is attained

Param.Name: SelfLevelling
Param.Description: This value dictates how much the helicopter self-levels with zero cyclic input (note this is not speed dependant)

Param.Name: StabilizerAngle
Param.Description: This is the downward angle in degrees of the rear horizontal stabilizer (which dictates natural forward-pitch flight angle tendency proportional to forward speed)

Param.Name: TailDiameter
Param.Description: The diameter of the tail rotor disc

Param.Name: WeatherVane
Param.Description: This value determines how much the tail naturally trails behind like the flight of a dart (works in conjunction with RudderPower)

Param.Name: waterFillRate
Param.Description: The rate at which water enters the vehicle once

Param.Name: AE_TailName
Param.Description: Event Name for Tail Rotor
